on this cell block questioned.

1465
01:52:09.139 --> 01:52:11.683
-Start with that friend of his.
-Who?

1466
01:52:11.850 --> 01:52:13.268
Him.

1467
01:52:14.269 --> 01:52:15.812
Open 237.

1468
01:52:19.316 --> 01:52:22.986
What do you mean , "He just wasn't here"?
Don't say that to me.

1469
01:52:23.862 --> 01:52:26.448
-Don't say that to me again .
-But, sir, he wasn't.

1470
01:52:26.657 --> 01:52:30.160
I can see that, Haig ! Think I'm blind?

1471
01:52:30.827 --> 01:52:32.412
Is that what you're saying?

1472
01:52:32.579 --> 01:52:35.082
-Am I blind , Haig?
-No, sir!

1473
01:52:35.999 --> 01:52:38.502
What about you. You blind?

1474
01:52:39.002 --> 01:52:41.546
-Tell me what this is.
-Last night's count.

1475
01:52:41.755 --> 01:52:45.050
You see Dufresne's name there?
I sure do. Right there.

1476
01:52:45.259 --> 01:52:46.593
"Dufresne."

1477
01:52:48.262 --> 01:52:51.014
He was in his cell at lights out.

1478
01:52:51.181 --> 01:52:54.101
Stands to reason he'd still be here
in the morning.

1479
01:52:54.434 --> 01:52:56.061
I want him found.

1480
01:52:56.270 --> 01:52:59.731
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!

1481
01:52:59.982 --> 01:53:01.191
Yes, sir.

1482
01:53:02.192 --> 01:53:05.988
Let's go. Move your butts. Move it!

1483
01:53:07.864 --> 01:53:08.865
Stand.

1484
01:53:10.284 --> 01:53:11.702
Well?

1485
01:53:14.788 --> 01:53:15.831
Well , what?

1486
01:53:15.998 --> 01:53:19.459
I see you two all the time.
You're thick as thieves, you are.

1487
01:53:20.544 --> 01:53:22.045
He must have said something.

1488
01:53:22.754 --> 01:53:25.674
No, sir, warden. Not a word.

1489
01:53:27.467 --> 01:53:30.053
Lord , it's a miracle!

1490
01:53:30.637 --> 01:53:33.223
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.

1491
01:53:33.890 --> 01:53:35.058
Nothing left...

1492
01:53:35.892 --> 01:53:38.603
... but some damn rocks
on a windowsill.

1493
01:53:38.812 --> 01:53:41.565
And that cupcake on the wall .
Let's ask her.

1494
01:53:41.732 --> 01:53:43.525
Maybe she knows.

1495
01:53:43.734 --> 01:53:46.486
What say there, fuzzy-britches?
Feel like talking?

1496
01:53:47.904 --> 01:53:49.239
Guess not.

1497
01:53:49.781 --> 01:53:51.992
Why should she be any different?

1498
01:53:53.076 --> 01:53:54.745
This is a conspiracy.

1499
01:53:55.370 --> 01:53:57.080
That's what this is.

1500
01:53:57.789 --> 01:54:01.543
One big , damn conspiracy!

1501
01:54:01.793 --> 01:54:03.795
And everyone's in on it!

1502
01:54:04.421 --> 01:54:05.589
Including her!

1503
01:54:40.624 --> 01:54:42.334
<i>In 1900...</i>

1504
01:54:42.542 --> 01:54:44.961
<i>...Andy Dufresne escaped...</i>

1505
01:54:45.128 --> 01:54:46.713
<i>...from Shawshank Prison.</i>

1506
01:54:48.965 --> 01:54:51.510
<i>All they found
was a muddy set of prison clothes...</i>

1507
01:54:52.135 --> 01:54:53.678
<i>...a bar of soap...</i>

1508
01:54:53.887 --> 01:54:55.472
<i>...and an old rock hammer...</i>

1509
01:54:55.639 --> 01:54:58.141
<i>...damn near worn down to the nub.</i>

1510
01:55:02.646 --> 01:55:07.401
<i>I remember thinking it would take a man
000 years to tunnel through the wall with it.</i>

1511
01:55:08.026 --> 01:55:10.654
<i>Old Andy did it in less than 20.</i>

1512
01:55:28.964 --> 01:55:31.258
<i>Oh, Andy loved geology.</i>

1513
01:55:32.008 --> 01:55:35.178
<i>I imagine it appealed to
his meticulous nature.</i>

1514
01:55:35.595 --> 01:55:37.431
<i>An ice age here...</i>

1515
01:55:37.848 --> 01:55:40.350
<i>...million years
of mountain-building there.</i>

1516
01:55:41.351 --> 01:55:44.187
<i>Geology is the study
of pressure and time.</i>

1517
01:55:45.021 --> 01:55:47.023
<i>That's all it takes, really.</i>

1518
01:55:47.774 --> 01:55:49.067
<i>Pressure...</i>

1519
01:55:49.526 --> 01:55:51.027
<i>...and time.</i>

1520
01:55:52.112 --> 01:55:54.197
<i>That and a big goddamn poster.</i>

1521
01:55:57.993 --> 01:55:59.161
<i>Like I said...</i>

1522
01:55:59.661 --> 01:56:03.665
<i>...in prison, a man will do anything
to keep his mind occupied.</i>

1523
01:56:06.460 --> 01:56:11.256
<i>Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting
his wall out into the exercise yard...</i>

1524
01:56:11.798 --> 01:56:13.717
<i>...a handful at a time.</i>

1525
01:56:15.051 --> 01:56:17.095
<i>I guess after Tommy was killed...</i>

1526
01:56:17.304 --> 01:56:20.265
<i>...Andy decided
he'd been here long enough.</i>

1527
01:56:20.474 --> 01:56:23.059
Lickety-split. I want to get home.

1528
01:56:23.768 --> 01:56:25.812
I'm just about finished , sir.

1529
01:56:47.250 --> 01:56:49.211
Three deposits tonight.

1530
01:56:56.510 --> 01:56:58.803
<i>Andy did like he was told.</i>

1531
01:56:59.012 --> 01:57:02.516
<i>Buffed those shoes
to a high mirror-shine.</i>

1532
01:57:06.186 --> 01:57:08.480
<i>The guards simply didn't notice.</i>

1533
01:57:08.772 --> 01:57:10.273
<i>Neither did I.</i>

1534
01:57:10.440 --> 01:57:11.983
<i>I mean, seriously...</i>

1535
01:57:12.192 --> 01:57:15.195
<i>...how often do you really look
at a man's shoes?</i>

1536
01:59:18.735 --> 01:59:21.905
<i>Andy crawled to freedom
through 500 yards...</i>

1537
01:59:22.155 --> 01:59:25.492
<i>...of shit-smelling foulness
I can't even imagine.</i>

1538
01:59:26.493 --> 01:59:28.828
<i>Or maybe I just don't want to.</i>

1539
01:59:33.249 --> 01:59:35.585
<i>Five hundred yards.</i>

1540
01:59:36.086 --> 01:59:39.172
<i>That's the length
of five football fields.</i>

1541
01:59:39.798 --> 01:59:42.384
<i>Just shy of half a mile.</i>

1542
02:00:37.605 --> 02:00:42.193
<i>The next morning, right about the time
Raquel was spilling her secret...</i>

1543
02:00:42.485 --> 02:00:45.321
<i>...a man nobody ever
laid eyes on before...</i>

1544
02:00:45.572 --> 02:00:48.158
<i>...strolled into
the Maine National Bank.</i>

1545
02:00:48.742 --> 02:00:51.911
<i>Until that moment, he didn't exist.</i>

1546
02:00:52.495 --> 02:00:54.831
<i>-Except on paper.</i>
-May I help you?

1547
02:00:55.248 --> 02:00:57.167
<i>He had all the proper ID--</i>

1548
02:00:57.375 --> 02:01:01.087
<i>Driver's license, birth certificate,
Social Security card.</i>

1549
02:01:01.504 --> 02:01:04.048
<i>--And the signature
was a spot-on match.</i>

1550
02:01:04.257 --> 02:01:07.343
I must say I'm sorry
to be losing your business.

1551
02:01:07.552 --> 02:01:09.304
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

1552
02:01:10.096 --> 02:01:11.681
Thank you.

1553
02:01:11.848 --> 02:01:13.016
I'm sure I will.

1554
02:01:13.933 --> 02:01:17.270
Here's your cashier's check, sir.
Will there be anything else?

1555
02:01:17.479 --> 02:01:18.480
Please.

1556
02:01:19.022 --> 02:01:21.524
Would you add this
to your outgoing mail?

1557
02:01:22.025 --> 02:01:23.568
I'd be happy to.

1558
02:01:25.028 --> 02:01:26.362
Good day, sir.

1559
02:01:27.322 --> 02:01:31.743
<i>Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks
in the Portland area that morning.</i>

1560
02:01:32.202 --> 02:01:33.828
<i>All told, he blew town...</i>

1561
02:01:34.037 --> 02:01:38.875
<i>...with better than $370, 000
of Warden Norton's money.</i>

1562
02:01:39.542 --> 02:01:42.337
<i>Severance pay for 19 years.</i>

1563
02:01:49.552 --> 02:01:51.763
Good morning , <i>Portland Daily Bugle.</i>

1564
02:02:44.607 --> 02:02:47.569
Byron Hadley?
You have the right to remain silent.

1565
02:02:47.819 --> 02:02:52.282
If you give up this right, anything you
say can be held against you in court.

1566
02:02:52.699 --> 02:02:57.161
<i>I wasn't there to see it, but I hear
Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...</i>

1567
02:02:57.370 --> 02:02:58.872
<i>...when they took him away.</i>

1568
02:03:04.752 --> 02:03:08.131
<i>Norton had no intention
of going that quietly.</i>

1569
02:03:24.105 --> 02:03:25.481
Samuel Norton.

1570
02:03:25.648 --> 02:03:28.067
We have a warrant for your arrest.
Open up.

1571
02:03:32.822 --> 02:03:34.282
Open the door.

1572
02:03:34.449 --> 02:03:35.700
I'm not sure which key.

1573
02:03:45.835 --> 02:03:47.795
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

1574
02:03:59.307 --> 02:04:02.769
<i>I like to think the last thing
that went through his head...</i>

1575
02:04:02.977 --> 02:04:04.562
<i>...other than that bullet...</i>

1576
02:04:04.771 --> 02:04:09.192
<i>...was to wonder how the hell
Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.</i>

1577
02:04:11.694 --> 02:04:15.198
<i>Not long after the warden
deprived us of his company...</i>

1578
02:04:15.448 --> 02:04:17.533
<i>...I got a postcard in the mail.</i>

1579
02:04:18.993 --> 02:04:21.829
<i>It was blank, but the postmark said...</i>

1580
02:04:22.038 --> 02:04:24.165
<i>...Fort Hancock, Texas.</i>

1581
02:04:24.707 --> 02:04:26.042
<i>Fort Hancock...</i>

1582
02:04:26.334 --> 02:04:28.044
<i>...right on the border.</i>

1583
02:04:28.461 --> 02:04:30.463
<i>That's where Andy crossed.</i>

1584
02:04:31.047 --> 02:04:35.176
<i>When I picture him heading south
in his own car with the top down...</i>

1585
02:04:35.510 --> 02:04:37.720
<i>...it always makes me laugh.</i>

1586
02:04:39.555 --> 02:04:41.140
<i>Andy Dufresne...</i>

1587
02:04:41.516 --> 02:04:43.559
<i>...who crawled through
a river of shit...</i>

1588
02:04:43.726 --> 02:04:46.145
<i>...and came out clean
on the other side.</i>

1589
02:04:46.980 --> 02:04:48.356
<i>Andy Dufresne...</i>

1590
02:04:49.148 --> 02:04:50.733
<i>...headed for the Pacific.</i>

1591
02:04:53.736 --> 02:04:55.905
Hadley's got him
by the throat, right?

1592
02:04:56.072 --> 02:04:59.909
He says, "I believe this boy's
about to have himself an accident."

1593
02:05:00.076 --> 02:05:02.954
<i>Those of us who knew him best
talk about him often.</i>

1594
02:05:03.621 --> 02:05:05.331
<i>I swear, the stuff he pulled. ...</i>

1595
02:05:05.540 --> 02:05:08.501
"My friends could use
a couple of beers."

1596
02:05:08.835 --> 02:05:10.503
And he got it!

1597
02:05:11.754 --> 02:05:14.132
<i>Sometimes it makes me sad, though...</i>

1598
02:05:14.424 --> 02:05:15.842
<i>...Andy being gone.</i>

1599
02:05:16.551 --> 02:05:20.680
<i>I have to remind myself that
some birds aren't meant to be caged.</i>

1600
02:05:21.139 --> 02:05:23.224
<i>Their feathers are just too bright.</i>

1601
02:05:24.934 --> 02:05:26.644
<i>And when they fly away...</i>

1602
02:05:27.103 --> 02:05:31.482
<i>...the part of you that knows it was
a sin to lock them up does rejoice.</i>

1603
02:05:32.567 --> 02:05:33.818
<i>But still...</i>

1604
02:05:34.277 --> 02:05:38.614
<i>...the place you live in is that much
more drab and empty that they're gone.</i>

1605
02:05:42.827 --> 02:05:45.204
<i>I guess I just miss my friend.</i>

1606
02:06:09.645 --> 02:06:10.813
Please sit down.

1607
02:06:16.652 --> 02:06:18.237
Ellis Boyd Redding ...

1608
02:06:18.780 --> 02:06:22.033
...your files say you've served
40 years of a life sentence.

1609
02:06:22.825 --> 02:06:24.994
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1610
02:06:26.829 --> 02:06:28.414
Rehabilitated?

1611
02:06:30.458 --> 02:06:32.335
Well , now, let me see.

1612
02:06:33.336 --> 02:06:35.671
I don't have any idea what that means.

1613
02:06:37.799 --> 02:06:40.051
It means you're ready
to rejoin society--

1614
02:06:40.635 --> 02:06:42.970
I know what you think it means, sonny.

1615
02:06:45.139 --> 02:06:47.141
To me it's just a made-up word.

1616
02:06:48.476 --> 02:06:50.812
A politician's word so that...

1617
02:06:51.229 --> 02:06:54.774
...young fellas like yourself
can wear a suit and a tie...

1618
02:06:55.233 --> 02:06:56.859
...and have a job.

1619
02:06:58.820 --> 02:07:00.905
What do you really want to know?

1620
02:07:01.697 --> 02:07:03.658
Am I sorry for what I did?

1621
02:07:04.075 --> 02:07:05.368
Well , are you?

1622
02:07:07.161 --> 02:07:09.997
There's not a day goes by
I don't feel regret.

1623
02:07:11.374 --> 02:07:14.836
Not because I'm in here
or because you think I should.

1624
02:07:18.297 --> 02:07:20.883
I look back on the way I was then ...

1625
02:07:23.010 --> 02:07:24.345
...a young ...

1626
02:07:25.263 --> 02:07:28.766
...stupid kid who committed
that terrible crime.

1627
02:07:31.769 --> 02:07:33.479
I want to talk to him.

1628
02:07:35.398 --> 02:07:37.900
I want to try
and talk some sense to him.

1629
02:07:38.609 --> 02:07:40.570
Tell him the way things are.

1630
02:07:42.655 --> 02:07:44.073
But I can't.

1631
02:07:46.284 --> 02:07:48.286
That kid's long gone...

1632
02:07:49.495 --> 02:07:52.248
...and this old man is all that's left.

1633
02:07:53.666 --> 02:07:55.126
I got to live with that.

1634
02:07:56.502 --> 02:07:58.212
Rehabilitated?

1635
02:07:58.588 --> 02:08:00.423
It's just a bullshit word.

1636
02:08:01.340 --> 02:08:06.095
So you go on and stamp your forms,
sonny, and stop wasting my time.

1637
02:08:07.346 --> 02:08:09.599
Because to tell you the truth ...

1638
02:08:09.932 --> 02:08:11.934
... I don't give a shit.

1639
02:09:38.479 --> 02:09:39.855
Here you go, miss.

1640
02:09:42.817 --> 02:09:43.859
Restroom break?

1641
02:09:49.657 --> 02:09:54.203
You don't need to ask me every time you
need to go take a piss. Just go.

1642
02:09:55.204 --> 02:09:56.831
Yes, sir.

1643
02:10:07.216 --> 02:10:10.303
<i>Forty years I've been asking
permission to piss.</i>

1644
02:10:11.137 --> 02:10:14.140
<i>I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.</i>

1645
02:10:17.643 --> 02:10:19.812
<i>There's a harsh truth to face.</i>

1646
02:10:21.480 --> 02:10:24.400
<i>No way I'm going to make it
on the outside.</i>

1647
02:10:32.241 --> 02:10:35.953
<i>All I do anymore is think of ways
to break my parole...</i>

1648
02:10:36.746 --> 02:10:39.248
<i>...so maybe they'd send me back.</i>

1649
02:10:44.420 --> 02:10:46.881
<i>Terrible thing, to live in fear.</i>

1650
02:10:47.757 --> 02:10:49.425
<i>Brooks Hatlen knew it.</i>

1651
02:10:49.633 --> 02:10:51.594
<i>Knew it all too well.</i>

1652
02:10:53.179 --> 02:10:56.599
<i>All I want is to be back
where things make sense.</i>

1653
02:10:57.016 --> 02:10:59.769
<i>Where I won't have to be afraid
all the time.</i>

1654
02:11:01.771 --> 02:11:04.106
<i>Only one thing stops me.</i>

1655
02:11:05.566 --> 02:11:07.943
<i>A promise I made to Andy.</i>

1656
02:11:28.464 --> 02:11:29.799
There it is.

1657
02:11:40.226 --> 02:11:41.894
Much obliged , sir.

1658
02:15:21.196 --> 02:15:22.489
<i>Dear Red:</i>

1659
02:15:22.698 --> 02:15:25.200
<i>if you're reading this,
you've gotten out...</i>

1660
02:15:25.367 --> 02:15:29.538
<i>...and if you've come this far,
maybe you're willing to come a bit further.</i>

1661
02:15:29.705 --> 02:15:32.207
<i>You remember the name
of the town, don't you?</i>

1662
02:15:34.501 --> 02:15:36.003
Zihuatanejo.

1663
02:15:37.630 --> 02:15:41.216
<i>I could use a good man
to help me get my project on wheels.</i>

1664
02:15:41.717 --> 02:15:45.262
<i>I'll keep an eye out for you,
and the chessboard ready.</i>

1665
02:15:46.055 --> 02:15:47.473
<i>Remember, Red...</i>

1666
02:15:47.806 --> 02:15:49.892
<i>...hope is a good thing...</i>

1667
02:15:50.100 --> 02:15:52.102
<i>...maybe the best of things.</i>

1668
02:15:52.311 --> 02:15:54.480
<i>And no good thing ever dies.</i>

1669
02:15:55.022 --> 02:15:57.900
<i>I will be hoping
that this letter finds you...</i>

1670
02:15:58.067 --> 02:15:59.818
<i>...and finds you well.</i>

1671
02:16:00.319 --> 02:16:01.570
<i>Your friend...</i>

1672
02:16:01.737 --> 02:16:02.905
<i>...Andy.</i>

1673
02:16:36.772 --> 02:16:38.482
<i>"Get busy living...</i>

1674
02:16:38.691 --> 02:16:40.609
<i>...or get busy dying."</i>

1675
02:16:43.278 --> 02:16:45.447
<i>That's goddamn right.</i>

1676
02:16:50.703 --> 02:16:52.830
<i>For the second time in my life...</i>

1677
02:16:53.080 --> 02:16:55.624
<i>...I'm guilty of committing a crime.</i>

1678
02:16:56.709 --> 02:16:58.627
<i>Parole violation.</i>

1679
02:16:59.294 --> 02:17:02.965
<i>Of course, I doubt they'll toss up
any roadblocks for that.</i>

1680
02:17:03.632 --> 02:17:05.676
<i>Not for an old crook like me.</i>

1681
02:17:05.884 --> 02:17:07.928
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

1682
02:17:11.598 --> 02:17:16.311
<i>I find I'm so excited I can barely
sit still or hold a thought in my head.</i>

1683
02:17:16.770 --> 02:17:20.107
<i>I think it's the excitement
only a free man can feel.</i>

1684
02:17:20.315 --> 02:17:22.818
<i>A free man at the start
of a long journey...</i>

1685
02:17:22.985 --> 02:17:25.612
<i>...whose conclusion is uncertain.</i>

1686
02:17:28.615 --> 02:17:31.285
<i>I hope I can make it across the border.</i>

1687
02:17:32.786 --> 02:17:35.831
<i>I hope to see my friend
and shake his hand.</i>

1688
02:17:37.666 --> 02:17:41.754
<i>I hope the Pacific is as blue
as it has been in my dreams.</i>

1689
02:17:43.589 --> 02:17:44.798
<i>I hope.</i>

